article:
This is a list of Baroque palaces built in Europe in the late 17th and 18th
centuries. Some of them were inspired by the construction of the Palace of
Versailles by Louis XIV and its successive extensions. Versailles was a source
of inspiration for the monarchs and nobles of Europe who also longed for a
residence appropriate to their privileged position.

Only the most important city residences, such as the Stockholm Palace and
Winter Palace, are included. Pre-Versailles Roman palazzi, such as Palazzo
Barberini, Palazzo Chigi-Odescalchi, Palazzo Ludovisi, Palazzo Colonna, Palazzo
Altieri, Palazzo Muti Papazzurri, Palazzo di Propaganda Fide, etc. are excluded
from this list.
